      "writtenOn": "2026-06-25T07:31:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How the deferred binding are supposed to be covered with the proposed interfaces?\n\nIt looks like RDE device somehow need to get absolute links for its root (EXTERNAL) resources.\n\nFor example for SmartNIC these resources can be points to enter:\n- `NetworkAdapterCollecion`\n- `NetworkIntefaceCollection`\n- `PCIeDeviceCollection`\n- `EthernetInterfaceCollecion`\nand for each of these resources RDE Device need to get full `/redfish/v1/...` strings, so they can be used in the deferred binding substitution, when method `PerformRedfishOperation` is invoked\n\nSee `91082: bej: add deferred binding substitution support` | https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/libbej/+/91082",
      "revId": "9f6802c2a6ccebc9ed80348436a0e52ab5c15a06",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a657ec5_7b0b8504",
        "filename": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/RDE/Manager.interface.yaml",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 23,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000926
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-24T15:45:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "RDE device can have many Redfish Resource PDR that report `ContainingResourceID\u003d0`  (0 in this case means \"EXTERNAL: This value is used to identify the logical root of a device component’s management topology\"). For example SmartNIC device can simultaniously report Redfish Resources that should be added to the different \"root\" collections on the server side:\n- `NetworkAdapterCollecion`\n- `NetworkIntefaceCollection`\n- `PCIeDeviceCollection`\n- `EthernetInterfaceCollecion`\n\nSo in other words just `TargetURI` is not enough, since all these resources will have \"/\" URI in this case.",
      "revId": "9f6802c2a6ccebc9ed80348436a0e52ab5c15a06",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
